   "source": [
    "### Loading the Raw Dataset\n",
    "\n",
    "The dataset contains 101,766 encounter records of diabetic patients collected across 130 U.S. hospitals from 1999 to 2008. It includes 50 features spanning demographics, diagnoses, medication usage, and prior hospital visits."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "df = load_dataset()\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape: {df.shape}\")\n",
    "df.head()"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Initial Data Cleaning\n",
    "\n",
    "Before building the full pipeline, we identify and remove low-quality records that would negatively impact model training. Two categories of rows are filtered out:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Rows with excessive missing values** \u2014 any record missing data in more than 30% of its columns is dropped, since imputation would be unreliable on such incomplete records.\n",
    "- **Records with invalid or ambiguous entries** \u2014 this includes encounters where all three diagnosis fields are empty, and the small number of records with an unrecognized gender value."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Identify rows where all diagnosis fields are missing \u2014 too little clinical info to use\n",
    "indices_to_drop = set()\n",
    "indices_to_drop.update(\n",
    "    list(df[df.diag_1.isna() & df.diag_2.isna() & df.diag_3.isna()].index)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Remove records with gender values that are neither Male nor Female\n",
    "indices_to_drop.update(\n",
    "    list(df[~df.gender.isin(['Male', 'Female'])].index)\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Records flagged for removal: {len(indices_to_drop)}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Apply initial cleaning steps via a pipeline for reproducibility\n",
    "initial_cleaning_pipeline = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    RowsNanFilter(),           # Drop rows missing >30% of attribute values\n",
    "    RowsFilter(indices_to_drop)  # Drop the specific flagged records\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "df = initial_cleaning_pipeline.fit_transform(df)\n",
    "print(f\"Dataset shape after initial cleaning: {df.shape}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Train / Test Split\n",
    "\n",
    "To prevent any information from the test set from leaking into the preprocessing steps, the 80/20 train/test split is performed before the main pipeline is applied. Class proportions are preserved using stratified sampling."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "X = df.drop('readmitted', axis=1)\n",
    "y = transform_label(df['readmitted'])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Class distribution:\\n{y.value_counts()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Early readmission rate: {y.mean():.2%}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(\n",
    "    X, y,\n",
    "    test_size=0.20,\n",
    "    random_state=42,\n",
    "    stratify=y  # Maintain class balance across both subsets\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Training set size : {X_train.shape[0]:,} records\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test set size     : {X_test.shape[0]:,} records\")\n",
    "X_train.head()"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Preprocessing Pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "The preprocessing pipeline was designed to be reproducible and self-contained so that any new dataset with the same schema can be passed through without manual adjustments. Based on our exploratory data analysis, the pipeline performs the following transformations:\n",
    "\n",
    "**Column-level filtering**\n",
    "- Remove columns with more than 45% missing values\n",
    "- Drop identifiers and administratively redundant columns (`encounter_id`, `patient_nbr`, `payer_code`)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Missing value imputation**\n",
    "- Categorical attributes: filled with the most frequent (mode) value\n",
    "- Numerical attributes: filled with the median value\n",
    "\n",
    "**Categorical consolidation**\n",
    "- Low-frequency categories (under 5% of records) are merged into a single `other` class to reduce noise\n",
    "\n",
    "**Low-diversity column removal**\n",
    "- Columns where one value appears in over 90% of rows are dropped (e.g., `examide`, `citoglipton`)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Ordinal encoding**\n",
    "- The `age` feature (originally stored as decade-range strings) is mapped to integers 0\u20139\n",
    "\n",
    "**Feature engineering**\n",
    "Three new features are derived from existing columns:\n",
    "- `visits_sum` \u2014 total number of prior emergency, outpatient, and inpatient encounters\n",
    "- `number_medicaments` \u2014 count of distinct diabetes medications prescribed\n",
    "- `number_medicaments_changes` \u2014 count of medications whose dosage was adjusted during the stay\n",
    "\n",
    "**Diagnosis categorization**\n",
    "- ICD-9 diagnosis codes (`diag_1`, `diag_2`, `diag_3`) are mapped to broad clinical categories (e.g., circulatory, respiratory, diabetes)\n",
    "\n",
    "**One-hot encoding**\n",
    "- All remaining categorical features are one-hot encoded to prepare data for any ML algorithm\n",
    "\n",
    "> After thorough analysis, we confirmed that normalization was not necessary for this dataset, and no extreme outliers warranted removal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Columns that carry no predictive signal for readmission\n",
    "columns_to_drop = ['encounter_id', 'patient_nbr', 'payer_code']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Columns with high cardinality categories that benefit from rare-class merging\n",
    "columns_to_reduce = ['discharge_disposition_id', 'admission_source_id']\n",
    "\n",
    "# Ordinal mapping: convert age decade-ranges to ordered integers\n",
    "ordinal_mappings = {\n",
    "    'age': {\n",
    "        '[0-10)': 0, '[10-20)': 1, '[20-30)': 2, '[30-40)': 3, '[40-50)': 4,\n",
    "        '[50-60)': 5, '[60-70)': 6, '[70-80)': 7, '[80-90)': 8, '[90-100)': 9\n",
    "    }\n",
    "}\n",
    "\n",
    "# Feature groups used in engineering steps\n",
    "visits_cols       = ['number_emergency', 'number_outpatient', 'number_inpatient']\n",
    "diagnoses_cols    = ['diag_1', 'diag_2', 'diag_3']\n",
    "medicaments_cols  = [\n",
    "    'metformin', 'repaglinide', 'nateglinide', 'chlorpropamide', 'glimepiride',\n",
    "    'acetohexamide', 'glipizide', 'glyburide', 'tolbutamide', 'pioglitazone',\n",
    "    'rosiglitazone', 'acarbose', 'miglitol', 'troglitazone', 'tolazamide',\n",
    "    'examide', 'citoglipton', 'insulin', 'glyburide-metformin',\n",
    "    'glipizide-metformin', 'glimepiride-pioglitazone',\n",
    "    'metformin-rosiglitazone', 'metformin-pioglitazone'\n",
    "]"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Separate feature columns by data type for targeted preprocessing\n",
    "categorical_features = X_train.select_dtypes(include=np.object_).columns.to_list()\n",
    "numerical_features   = X_train.select_dtypes(exclude=np.object_).columns.to_list()\n",
    "non_medication_cols  = list(set(X_train.columns) - set(medicaments_cols))\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Categorical features : {len(categorical_features)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Numerical features   : {len(numerical_features)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Medication columns   : {len(medicaments_cols)}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Full preprocessing pipeline with four main branches\n",
    "preprocessing_pipeline = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    # Step 1: Remove unwanted columns upfront\n",
    "    ColumnsFilter(columns_to_drop),\n",
    "    ColumnsNanFilter(),  # Drop columns with >45% missing values\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Steps 2\u20134: Parallel feature branches merged at the end\n",
    "    PandasFeatureUnion([\n",
    "        # Branch A: Numerical feature processing\n",
    "        ('numerical_features', make_pipeline(\n",
    "            ColumnsFilter(categorical_features),    # Keep only numeric cols\n",
    "            MissingValuesImputer(strategy='median'),\n",
    "            NumberVisitsCreator(visits_cols),       # Create visits_sum feature\n",
    "        )),\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Branch B: Categorical feature processing\n",
    "        ('categorical_features', make_pipeline(\n",
    "            ColumnsFilter(numerical_features),      # Keep only categorical cols\n",
    "            DiagnosesCodesMapper(diagnoses_cols),   # Map ICD-9 codes to categories\n",
    "            MissingValuesImputer(strategy='most_frequent'),\n",
    "            SmallCategoriesReducer(exclude_columns=['age']),\n",
    "            ColumnsValuesDiversityFilter(0.9),      # Drop near-constant columns\n",
    "            ValueMapper(ordinal_mappings),           # Encode age as integer\n",
    "            OneHotEncoder(exclude_columns=['age'])\n",
    "        )),\n",
    "\n",
    "        # Branch C: Medication-based feature engineering\n",
    "        ('medicaments_features', make_pipeline(\n",
    "            ColumnsFilter(non_medication_cols),     # Isolate medication columns\n",
    "            NumberMedicamentsChangesCreator(medicaments_cols),\n",
    "            NumberMedicamentsCreator(medicaments_cols),\n",
    "            ColumnsFilter(medicaments_cols)         # Drop raw medication flags\n",
    "        ))\n",
    "    ])\n",
    ")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Fit on training data only \u2014 transform both subsets\n",
    "X_train_prep = preprocessing_pipeline.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test_prep  = preprocessing_pipeline.transform(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Features after preprocessing: {X_train_prep.shape[1]}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Training records            : {X_train_prep.shape[0]:,}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Test records                : {X_test_prep.shape[0]:,}\")"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Verify no missing values remain in the age column\n",
    "missing_age = X_train_prep.age.isna().sum()\n",
    "print(f\"Missing values in 'age' after preprocessing: {missing_age}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Confirm all features are numeric (required for all ML algorithms used)\n",
    "print(\"\\nFeature data types:\")\n",
    "print(X_train_prep.dtypes.value_counts())"
   ],
   "outputs": [],
   "execution_count": null
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
