  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Summary\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook established a complete, reproducible preprocessing pipeline for the diabetic patient readmission dataset. The key outcomes are:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Data cleaning** removed low-quality rows and uninformative columns, improving dataset reliability.\n",
    "- **Missing value handling** applied median imputation for numerical features and mode imputation for categorical ones.\n",
    "- **Feature engineering** introduced three new variables (`visits_sum`, `number_medicaments`, `number_medicaments_changes`) that capture patient history more directly.\n",
    "- **Diagnosis mapping** condensed hundreds of ICD-9 codes into meaningful clinical categories, reducing noise.\n",
    "- **Encoding** converted all categorical features to numeric form, making the data compatible with the Random Forest, XGBoost, and MLP models evaluated in Capstone 1.\n",
    "\n",
    "The structured pipeline ensures results are reproducible and the same transformations can be consistently applied to any new batch of patient data."
   ]
  }
